dct_alternative_sm: Pei Ho (Hai Ho) or Peking (Peiping) River
dct_description_sm: From surveys by the Hai Ho Conservatory Commision between 1905 and 1930 ; Depths on the bar, inside the 12 ft. curve, are from the 1921 Report of the Commission; from Deep Hole to Quarantine Sta., they are from Chinese Admiralty chart of 1931.
Depths shown by soundings and isolines.
Shows approach depths, drainage, various objects/facilities, roads.
Notes on tidal currents, depths, docks.
Descriptive text, such as "Flat muddy foreshore sprinkled with shells."
